<subSubSection pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="72.[264,1323,283,590]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,440,283,309]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[462,685,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvigena">
<emphasis box="[462,685,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Geostiba silvigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other Nearctic species of 
<taxonomicName box="[264,370,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[264,370,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Geostiba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having large eyes (temple length to eye length ratio 
<number box="[1021,1061,324,350]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" value="2.3">2.3</number>
), pronotal pubescence of 
<typeStatus box="[296,346,364,390]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">type</typeStatus>
V, well developed wings, long elytra (pronotum length to elytron length ratio 1.0), the presence of two short parallel carinae in the middle of male abdominal tergum 
<quantity box="[1273,1321,404,430]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="in" value="7.0">7 in</quantity>
front of posterior margin, and the shape of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[932,1100,444,470]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 321 ­ 326" captionStart-1="FIGURES 327 ­ 335" captionStartId-0="72.[264,383,1696,1720]" captionStartId-1="73.[264,383,1480,1504]" captionTargetBox-0="[286,1297,660,1656]" captionTargetBox-1="[307,1280,824,1441]" captionTargetId-0="figure@72.[275,1311,649,1670]" captionTargetId-1="figure@73.[296,1290,809,1454]" captionTargetPageId-0="72" captionTargetPageId-1="73" captionText-0="FIGURES 321 ­ 326. Abdominal segment 8 and aedeagus of Geostiba silvigena Gusarov, sp. n. (holotype). 321 – male tergum 8; 322 – male sternum 8; 323 – median lobe, ventral view; 324 – apex of median lobe, ventral view; 325 – median lobe, lateral view; 326 – apex of median lobe, lateral view. Scale bar 0.4 mm (321 ­ 323, 325), 0.2 mm (324, 326)." captionText-1="FIGURES 327 ­ 335. Genitalia of Geostiba silvigena Gusarov, sp. n. (holotype). 327 – details of internal sac retracted into median lobe, ventral view; 328 – copulatory piece of internal sac, dorsal view; 329 – distal diverticula of everted internal sac, ventral view; 330 – everted internal sac, ventral view; 331 – everted internal sac, lateral view; 332 ­ 333 – details of internal sac retracted into median lobe, lateral view; 334 – apex of left paramere, side facing median lobe; 335 – copulatory piece of internal sac, lateral view. Scale bar 0.4 mm (327, 330 ­ 333), 0.2 mm (328 ­ 329, 334 ­ 335)." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/155746/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/155747/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
Figs. 
<number box="[998,1100,444,470]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" value="329.0" valueMax="335.0" valueMin="323.0">323­335</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="72.[264,1323,283,590]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicName box="[312,533,484,509]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvigena">
<emphasis box="[312,533,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Geostiba silvigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to eastern Nearctic 
<taxonomicName box="[964,1176,484,509]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="appalachigena">
<emphasis box="[964,1176,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">G. appalachigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and differs only in having the apex of median lobe less bent ventrally (in lateral view) (
<figureCitation box="[1152,1319,524,550]" captionStart="FIGURES 321 ­ 326" captionStartId="72.[264,383,1696,1720]" captionTargetBox="[286,1297,660,1656]" captionTargetId="figure@72.[275,1311,649,1670]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="FIGURES 321 ­ 326. Abdominal segment 8 and aedeagus of Geostiba silvigena Gusarov, sp. n. (holotype). 321 – male tergum 8; 322 – male sternum 8; 323 – median lobe, ventral view; 324 – apex of median lobe, ventral view; 325 – median lobe, lateral view; 326 – apex of median lobe, lateral view. Scale bar 0.4 mm (321 ­ 323, 325), 0.2 mm (324, 326)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/155746/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
Figs. 
<number box="[1218,1264,524,550]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" value="325.0">325</number>
­326
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[264,336,564,590]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 ­ 37" captionStartId="21.[264,383,1148,1172]" captionTargetBox="[321,1268,571,1127]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[319,1272,569,1127]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 34 ­ 37. Aedeagus of Geostiba appalachigena Gusarov, sp. n. (paratype from Black Mountain, West Virginia). 34 – median lobe, ventral view; 35 – apex of median lobe, ventral view; 36 – median lobe, lateral view; 37 – apex of median lobe, lateral view. Scale bar 0.2 mm (34, 36), 0.1 mm (35, 37)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/155708/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
36­ 
<number box="[305,336,564,590]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" value="37.0">37</number>
</figureCitation>
), and longer and more narrow apex of paramere (
<figureCitation box="[916,1029,564,590]" captionStart="FIGURES 327 ­ 335" captionStartId="73.[264,383,1480,1504]" captionTargetBox="[307,1280,824,1441]" captionTargetId="figure@73.[296,1290,809,1454]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURES 327 ­ 335. Genitalia of Geostiba silvigena Gusarov, sp. n. (holotype). 327 – details of internal sac retracted into median lobe, ventral view; 328 – copulatory piece of internal sac, dorsal view; 329 – distal diverticula of everted internal sac, ventral view; 330 – everted internal sac, ventral view; 331 – everted internal sac, lateral view; 332 ­ 333 – details of internal sac retracted into median lobe, lateral view; 334 – apex of left paramere, side facing median lobe; 335 – copulatory piece of internal sac, lateral view. Scale bar 0.4 mm (327, 330 ­ 333), 0.2 mm (328 ­ 329, 334 ­ 335)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/155747/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Figs. 334</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1041,1075,564,590]" captionStart="FIGURES 38 ­ 50" captionStartId="22.[264,383,1403,1427]" captionTargetBox="[306,1285,460,1385]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[294,1294,449,1393]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 38 ­ 50. Genitalia of Geostiba appalachigena Gusarov, sp. n. (paratypes from Black Mountain (38, 40 ­ 45, 47 ­ 50) and Back Allegheny Mountain (39, 46), West Virginia). 38 – details of internal sac retracted into median lobe, ventral view; 39 – copulatory piece of internal sac, dorsal view; 40 – medial lamellae of internal sac, ventral view; 41 distal diverticula of everted internal sac, ventral view; 42 – everted internal sac, ventral view; 43 – spermatheca; 44 ­ 45 – details of internal sac retracted into median lobe, lateral view; 46 – copulatory piece of internal sac, lateral view; 47 – medial lamella of internal sac, lateral view; 48 – everted internal sac, lateral view; 49 – right distal diverticulum of everted internal sac, lateral view; 50 – apex of left paramere, side facing median lobe. Scale bar 0.2 mm (38, 42, 44 ­ 45, 48), 0.1 mm (39 ­ 41, 43, 46 ­ 47, 49 ­ 50)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/155709/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">50</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
